gomodel:SYNGO_571  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Spine morphology of medium spiny neurons in striatal sections obtained from WAVE1-/- mice revealed that WAVE1-/- neurons displayed a significant reduction in class 1 spines (stubby type), class 2 spines (comprised of mature spines with a relatively large head and a short neck) and class 3 spines (thin spines) and showed a relatively high density of class 4 protrusions, or filopodia.\n\nFurthermore WAVE1 RNAi in primary hippocampal neurons resulted in a decrease in the density of class 2 spines and an increase in filopodia.\n\n30/8/2017 Pim\n- Fig.1 WAVE1 co-ips with actin\n- Fig.2 Inhibition of Arp2/3-complex-mediated actin polymerization by phosphorylation of WAVE1.. Experimental description: male C57BL/6 mice (6-8 weeks old)\n\n30/8/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed WAVE1 was human species: \"Human WAVE1 cDNA28 was subcloned into pCMV-Myc (BD)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_571" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
